text:
Clean school years, remove string column

PEN_columns &lt;- PEN_data |&gt; 
  mutate(year = str_extract(school_year, "\\d{4}-\\d{4}")) |&gt; 
  select(!school_year)

PEN_columns |&gt; 
  arrange(desc(year))

Export Data

PEN_files_clean |&gt; 
  write_rds("data-processed/PEN-files.rds")

Clean Dates

state_dates &lt;- state_clean |&gt; 
  mutate(
    date_removed_challenged = ymd(date_of_challenge_removal)
  ) 

state_dates

Remove Columns

clean_states &lt;- state_dates |&gt; 
  select(!c(secondary_author_s,illustrator_s,translator_s,series,date_of_challenge_removal))

Export Clean Data

clean_states |&gt; 
  write_rds("data-processed/statewide-ban.rds")

Join Ban Status and Ban Type column; Series and Series Name

PEN_ban_type &lt;- PEN_columns |&gt; 
  mutate(ban_standing = if_else(is.na(type_of_ban), ban_status, type_of_ban)) |&gt; 
  select(!c(ban_status, type_of_ban)) 


PEN_files_clean &lt;- PEN_ban_type |&gt; 
  mutate(book_series = if_else(is.na(series), series_name, series)) |&gt; 
  select(!c(series, series_name))

Which author has the most banned books overall?

PEN_files |&gt; 
  group_by(author) |&gt; 
  summarise(appearances = n()) |&gt; 
  arrange(desc(appearances))






Data Takeaway:
Ellen Hopkins, Sarah J. Mass and Stephen King have been the top three most commonly banned authors between the 2021-22 and 2024-25 school years. Ellen Hopkins has the most banned titles, with 435 of her books banned across school districts nationwide. Sarah J. Mass has 338 titles banned, and Stephen King has 219 titles banned across school districts.

